# Frontend React Conventions

## Style
- Functional components only, no class components
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` unless absolutely necessary
- Import types from `@swagger-aggregator/shared` (shared package)
- Use `type` imports for type-only imports (`import type { ... }`)

## State Management
- TanStack Query for server state (fetching, caching, mutations)
- React state (`useState`) for local UI state only
- No Redux or Zustand — keep it simple

## API Calls
- All API calls go through `@swagger-aggregator/shared` functions
- Never call axios directly in components
- Use custom hooks in `hooks/` for TanStack Query wrappers

## Component Structure
```
components/   — Reusable UI components
pages/        — Route pages (one per route)
hooks/        — Custom hooks (TanStack Query wrappers)
lib/          — Utilities (API setup, token storage)
```

## Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind v4 utility classes directly
- Custom theme variables defined in `index.css` (:root)
- No CSS modules or styled-components
